<http://model.geneontology.org/5fce9b7300002524/600ced8500000423> a ns4:GO_0097400,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    ns2:x "3666"^^xsd:string ;
    ns2:y "1009"^^xsd:string ;
    dc:contributor "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7476-6306"^^xsd:string,
        "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3394-9805"^^xsd:string ;
    dc:date "2021-08-06"^^xsd:string ;
    ns1:providedBy "http://informatics.jax.org"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:comment """ While
WT Act1 was able to restore IL-17-induced IκBα phosphorylation and degradation, JNK
and ERK phosphorylation in Act1
−/
−
 MEFs, the D-Ubox mutant showed much reduced
activity (Fig. 2C). Theses data demonstrate that the U-box domain of Act1 is indeed
important for IL-17-mediated signalling, implicating the importance of U-box-mediated E3
ubiquitin ligase activity in IL-17-induced Act1-mediated signalling."""^^xsd:string,
        "Through the use of the Ubc13-Uev1A E2 complex, Act1 mediated the lysine-63-linked ubiquitination of tumor necrosis factor receptor-associated factor 6 (TRAF6), a component of IL-17-mediated signaling. "^^xsd:string .

